[{"id": "a6ce91d0-b28a-4af3-83c8-6f7606c7b0d2", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "USER: Hi, a friend sent me this app to test out. where do I start?\nASSISTANT: Hey! Welcome in.\n\nYou're looking at a character selection screen \u2014 I'm one of three built-in demos. Pick one and you're off.\n\nQuick orientation:\n- **Characters** are your entry point. Each one has its own system prompt, world context, writing instructions. You can edit any of these or build your own from scratch.\n- **Anchors** are the magic trick \u2014 keyword-triggered lore that injects mid-conversation. Character knows it's been revealed, too. Great for mysteries, slow-burn worldbuilding.\n- **RAG memory** runs automatically. Your chat history is searchable by meaning, not just exact words. All local.\n- **Style Overseer** reviews every response against rules you write in plain English. \"No modern slang in fantasy settings\" kind of thing.\n\nIf you want to just play around, open Hermione and write something \u2014 she's configured for actual HP fiction. If you want to see how configs work, poke around in her settings.\n\nWhat are you looking to do? Write something, or figure out how the pieces fit?", "embedding": [-0.05946210399270058, -0.048603516072034836, 0.016138551756739616, -0.04629147797822952, -0.04912995919585228, -0.01465810276567936, 0.022121841087937355, 0.036853063851594925, -0.004258328583091497, -0.010458752512931824, -0.02002534829080105, -0.042772211134433746, -0.00815080851316452, -0.03561365604400635, -0.01430791337043047, 0.030288290232419968, 0.08031103760004044, -0.04470764845609665, -0.017575109377503395, 0.024285592138767242, 0.016140585765242577, -0.008047564886510372, 0.06375720351934433, 0.01968350261449814, 0.02371719479560852, -0.024988269433379173, -0.013497917912900448, 0.05014350265264511, -0.05020635202527046, -0.0035493976902216673, -0.019417839124798775, 0.05870916321873665, 0.024972086772322655, 0.07033270597457886, -0.0256812684237957, 0.06497327983379364, 0.0268