hreads- I really want to try out Lagoon but I'm curious if the Venice key is a hard requirement. I have a full local setup with kobold, but I've been fighting context demons in Sillytavern for so long (I'm tired, boss) that I'm cool with getting a key if needed. I just prefer keeping things local for privacy reasons.\n\n\n\n\nUser Avatar\nSlap_Shot1987\n12:48 PM\nit's not a hard requirement.\n\nVenice key is not required \u2014 Lagoon supports:\n- Ollama (local, fully private)\n- Custom endpoint (anything OpenAI-compatible \u2014 KoboldCPP, LM Studio, TabbyAPI, etc.)\n- Venice (optional, cloud)\n- Together.ai (optional, cloud)\n\nBut... I can't test that myself as I don't have a local setup. And, I'm currently making it bulletproof for local setups.\n\nWindows or Linux?\nASSISTANT: Good catch on the Windows/Linux question. If they're running Kobold, that's almost certainly local \u2014 and they're exactly the user profile that's been asking for OpenAI-compatible endpoint support.\n\nThis tells you a few things:\n\n1. **Privacy-first users are real.** They'll get a key if they have to, but they'd rather not. The fact that Lagoon supports custom endpoints matters to them.\n\n2. **SillyTavern fatigue is real.** \"Context demons\" \u2014 they're tired of fighting ST's context management. That's your wedge. Your RAG memory + anchor system + summary stack is the alternative you can pitch.\n\n3. **You need someone with a local setup testing.** You said you don't have one. If downwardspiral is your only early access person and they're on local/Kobold, you're relying on them to tell you what's broken. That's fine for one tester, but it's a gap.\n\nWhat's the custom endpoint implementation look like right now? Is it just a URL field in settings, or is there more configuration involved (API key field for things like TabbyAPI that might need it, etc.)?", "embedding": [0.005948242731392384, -0.06398860365152359, 0.008005735464394093, -0.03550386428833008, -0.008410041220486164, 